<HTML>
<HEAD>
 <TITLE>Chernobyl 11+</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<H2><IMG SRC=../images/chern11.gif ALT="" HEIGHT=50 WIDHT=50 BORDER=0> Chernobyl 11+</H2>

<H3>Stop western nuclear lobby moving east</H3>


<P><B>2500 KM PARADE FOR MOTHER EARTH<BR>
 BRUSSELS  -  MOCHOVCE NPP<BR>
 April 26th => August 20th 1997</B>
</P>

<P>Gent,  November 14th 1996 - Eleven years after the Chernobyl
disaster, on Saturday April 26th 1997, For Mother Earth launches a
2500km anti-nuclear parade at the EU in Brussels. The parade ends on
August 20th in Slovakia, at the construction site of the Mochovce
nuclear power plant (NPP). The partici- pants of the Parade demand
the immediate halt of the western nuclear industry moving to Central
and Eastern Europe (CEE).  For Mother Earth denounces the promotion
of atomic power by the EU (Euratom) and the IAEA (International
Atomic Energy Agency).</P>

<P>In the aftermath of the Chernobyl disaster most construction
plans were cancelled in the Western world. However, today we
notice that the Western atomic lobby makes huge profits buil-
ding new NPP and upgrading existing ones, under seriously
reduced safety rules, in CEE.</P>

<P>Tom Keunen, the parade's main organiser from Belgium states
that 'Eleven years after Chernobyl, solidarity between the
European people to stop this dangerous business is crucial.
The parade is an important tool where western, central and
eastern european will meet and share their concerns and visi-
ons. We have to act before a new Chernobyl.'</P>

<P>The Parade will start in Brussels, and go to Germany to sup-
port the international consumers boycott and campaign against
the German corporation Siemens. The Siemens multinational is a
major force in the completion of the Mochovce NPP in Slovakia.</P>

<P>In the Czech Republic the activists will join the ongoing
national campaign of Hnuti Duha (CZ Friends of the Earth)
against the completion of the Temelin NPP. This ex-Soviet
plant is to be finished by Westinghouse and ExIm Bank (USA)
and Skoda Nuclear (CZ). The participants will join 'Clean
Energy Brigades' (energy efficiency housing program) and a
non-violent direct action week at the NPP.</P>

<P>In Vienna (Austria) the activists will hand over ten thousands
of signatures at the IAEA HQ  demanding to stop the promotion
of atomic energy by this UN agency, and to set up an new UN
Agency to promote renewable energies. This petition was laun-
ched last spring by Abolition 2000 - a Global Network to
Eliminate Nuclear Weapons.</P>
 
<P>The parade will end on August 5th at the construction site
of the Mochovce Nuclear Power Plant, where they will join Za
Matku Zem's (FME Slovakia) 'Clean Energy Brigades' followed by
a week of direct actions. The construction of this ex-Soviet
NPP gets financed by Siemens (Germany) and Framatome (France).</P>

<P>The parade will end with meetings to plan the next steps
to halt the nuclear industry moving to CEE.</P>

<P>You can join the parade by foot, by bicycle, or by a renewable
energy vehicle. The parade will move aprox. 25km/day, six days a
week. The Dutch collective Rampenplan will provide
delicious vegetarian and vegan food.</P>

<P>=>What can you do?</P>

<P><UL>
 <LI>Participate in the PARADE FOR MOTHER EARTH  More info and
  registration forms available! 
 <LI>Participate in the Clean Energy Brigades and the direct action
  camps in Temelin and Mochovce. 
 <LI>Collect signatures for Siemens and IAEA-reform petitions.  
 <LI>Invite us to organize an info-meeting in YOUR neighbourhood.  
 <LI>Buy and sell sponsor-materials (ask list).   
 <LI>Support the Clean Energy Brigade financially (converting one
  house in CEE into a sustainable house costs about 45 DM).
 <LI>Support the parade or the actioncamps with a generous dona   
  tion. (Especially as many participants will come from Central and
  Eastern Europe) 
</UL></P>

<P>More information: <A HREF="mailto:tom@motherearth.knooppunt.be">tom@motherearth.knooppunt.be</A></P>

<P><A HREF=../index.html><IMG SRC=../images/home.gif ALT="Back to Homepage" BORDER=0><A HREF=../actidx.html><IMG SRC=../images/actions.gif ALT="Back to Campaign page" BORDER=0></A></P>  

<HR SIZE=3>
