<HTML>
<HEAD>
 <TITLE>Siemens involvement in the Mochovce NPP</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<H2><IMG SRC=../images/mochovce.gif ALT="" HEIGHT=50 WIDHT=50 BORDER=0></H2>

<H3>Siemens involvement in the Mochovce Nuclear Power Plant</H3>

<P>Where as less expensive, less environmentally damaging and less
dangerous solutions exist to solve the energy requirements of Slovakia
than Mochovce.</P>

<P>Where as the Slovak government has consistently contradicted itself
about the closure of the older Bohunice nuclear power plant being
linked to the opening of Mochovce plant and has refused to sign any
binding agreements that would link these two event considered
necessary by the German government, the EBRD and the European
Parliament. (Bayernwerke chief Eberhard Wild even said ,Certainly, no
one would allow us to build this installation in the vicinity of
Munich.")</P>

<P>Whereas both Preussen Elektra and Bayernwerke withdrew from the
Mochovce project because they could not be assured the project would
be safely completed.</P>

<P>Where as the German government (which plans to insure the Siemens
component of the Mochovce project through their Hermes Export Import
Bank) refused to allow the continued operation of the Greifswald
reactor of same design after unification, because it could not be
safely operated nor economically upgraded.  And the German government
reject plans to complete unfinished Greifswald reactors at nearly the
same level of completion as Mochovce, because they could not be
economically and safely operated.</P>

<P>Whereas the European Parliament resolved in a vote of 196 to 40 that
financing for the Mochovce project should only be granted under the
following conditions: 
<UL>
 <LI>verification by Euratom that EU safety standards are strictly 
 applied
 <LI>establishment of a contractually binding timetable ensuring the
 closure of blocs 1 and 2 of the Bohunice  nuclear power plant and an
 evaluation of the security situation in the other blocks of this plant
 <LI>the holding of a public hearing in Austria according to the rules 
 laid down by in the ESPOO Convention
 <LI>the clarification of the question which long term arrangements 
 are foreseen for the disposal of nuclear waste
</UL>

<P>None of these conditions have been met to date, nor does the Slovak
power utility appear interested in satisfying any of them.</P>

<P>Where as the estimated costs and completion schedule for Mochovce are
totally unrealistic and the economic resources consumed by this
project will seriously damage the development of Slovakia.</P>

<P>Where as the Slovak government continually use the Siemens involvement
to justify that the project will be safe enough to operate and
withdrawal of Siemens would significantly increase the chances the
project was not completed.</P>

<P>Be it resolved that the undersigned organizations and personalities
demand that Siemens should withdraw from the Mochovce project and 
international pressure be put on Slovakia's decision makers at all 
levels to pursue a non-nuclear energy development path.</P>

<P><A HREF=../index.html><IMG SRC=../images/home.gif ALT="Back to Homepage" BORDER=0><A HREF=../actidx.html><IMG SRC=../images/actions.gif ALT="Back to Campaign page" BORDER=0></A></P>  

<HR SIZE=3>
