<HTML>
<HEAD>
 <TITLE>Charter of For Mother Earth</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<H1><IMG SRC=images/aboutfme.gif ALT="" BORDER=0> Charter of For Mother Earth</H1>

<P>Following is the new and approved charter of For Mother Earth 
International as consensed upon on the General Meeting, April 15th 
1996, Kiev, Ukraine. People from the following countries attended
this  meeting: Belarus, Belgium, Denmark, Germany, Finland,
Netherlands,  Rumania, Slovakia and the Ukraine.</P> 

<H2>1 - WHO</H2>
<P>FOR MOTHER EARTH is a non-violent, international, non-profit 
citizens organisation, which takes initiatives to promote human rights, 
disarmament and protection of the environment and all creatures, 
from the premise of an understanding that the Earth is a creation to be 
honored and respected as our Mother.</P>

<H2>2 - CAMPAIGNS</H2>

<H3>2.1 - INTERNATIONAL CAMPAIGNS</H3>
<P>FOR MOTHER EARTH its main international campaign is anti-nuclear. 
FOR MOTHER EARTH calls attention to social, medical, ecological, 
economical and political consequences of the Atomic Age, with special 
attention for human rights violations of Indigenous Peoples. FOR 
MOTHER EARTH gives concrete examples of alternatives with special 
attention to and emphasis on non-violence, sustainable ways of life and 
renewable energy technologies.
New international campaigns are decided by the general meeting.</P>

<H3>2.2 - NATIONAL/REGIONAL CAMPAIGNS</H3>
<P>FOR MOTHER EARTH national/regional campaigns are decided by 
respective groups, according the regional needs and possibilities.</P>

<H2>3 - DECISION MAKING</H2>
<P>Direct democracy based on consensus decision-making (for example 
shared leadership) and non-violent conflict-resolution are the political 
choices in our path to reach our goals. International decisions 
(structure, working groups, campaigns, finances,...) are made at an 
annual international general meeting with as many activists as 
possible from all FOR MOTHER EARTH groups. Those unable to attend 
could name other FME- activists to communicate their messages, or 
send written communications, and try to arrange communication for 
duing the meeting.</P>
<P>For urgencies other means of communication (i.e. e-mail) can be used 
effectively to decide on common campaigns (i.e. the boycott of French 
nuclear testing). Decisions of the general meeting are facilitated by 
members of different FME-groups.</P>

<H2>4 - INTERNATIONAL OFFICE</H2>

<P>At this moment the office in Gent (Belgium) has a facilitating role for 
the international work. Division of tasks, and rotation of the 
international office is encouraged.</P>

<H2>5 - FINANCES</H2>

<P>FOR MOTHER EARTH groups are self-sufficient with their finances 
and shall support each other as much as possible. The international 
office of FOR MOTHER EARTH is self-sufficient and makes maximum 
use of the network (for example merchandise-exchange, mail).</P>

<A HREF=index.html><IMG SRC=images/home.gif ALT="Back to Homepage" BORDER=0></A>  

<HR SIZE=3>
<FONT SIZE=-2>
<address>&copy '94/'96 For Mother Earth International
</address></font></BODY></HTML>



