<H1>Racist bombattack in Polynesia</H1>
<FONT SIZE=-1><A HREF=pr04.html><IMG SRC=./~fme/images/flag_nl.gif BORDER=0> Dutch version of this press release</A></FONT><P>

<H3> Actions at French Embassies and Consulates</H3>

Gent, October 28th 1995 - After the third French nuclear test FOR
MOTHER EARTH International calls consumers and business-owners
one more time to join the international boycott of French
products and services.<P>

<H3>Racist bombattack</H3>
According to FOR MOTHER EARTH every new nuclear test is a racist
bombattack against the Indigenous Maohi population of Polynesia,
who rightfully wonder why the French don't detonate their nuclear
bombs in France if they aren't harmfull for health and
environment. According to FME's spokesperson Pol D'Huyvetter 'the
main goal of the boycott is to sent a strong signal to the French
population which reacts very mild. FME understands the concern
of the French with about the new wave of bombattacks in Paris.
However it's time for them to realize that the French politicians
commit atomic bombattacks against the Indigenous people of
Polynesia. Since 1945, in average, every nine days a nuclear test
took place on Earth, and all of them where on the lands of
Indigenous People", states Pol. 'Consumers and business-owners
can, by participating in this boycott send a strong signal to
Paris and the French population, and declare solidarity with the
Maohi who call for this boycott.'<P>


<H3>Monday october 30th</H3>
FOR MOTHER EARTH  will call her members and symphatizers to
participate in a vigil organised by the Test Stop Coalition
(gathering 80 organisations in Belgium). This will take place at
the French Embassy in Brussels, monday october 30th at 12h00, or
at the French Consulats in their neighbourhood (Gent and
Antwerp).<P>

<H3>  International</H3>
FOR MOTHER EARTH groups in the Netherlands, Slovakia, Belarus and
the USA will also be requested to make actions at the same time
in their country.<P>

<H3>Non-violent direct action</H3>
In Belgium FOR MOTHER EARTH will prepare, together with the War
Resistors International, a non-violent direct action to condemn
this new bombattack against the Polynesian population and all
Life.<P>

</DL>
<HR>
</TD></TABLE>
