<H1>Letter from Maohi People</H1>

From HITI TAU<BR>

Network of the Pacific Island Association of Non Government
Organisation  PIANGO<BR>
P.B.4611 PAPEETE  TAHITI   French Polynesia<BR>
Tel.  : (689) 521371 / Fax : (689) 572880<P>

<H1>SUPPORT THE MAOHI'S PROTEST AGAINST THE RESUMPTION 
OF NUCLEAR TESTING AT MURUROA AND FANGATOUFA</H1>

     We, the Maohi's, the native people of the Polynesian
archipelago, ask all our brothers and sisters of the Pacific
Ocean and the rest of the world for support, in order to enforce
our legal demands for self-determination:<P>

- the immediate halt of nuclear testing on our territory;<P>

- the creation of an international research commission to
investigate health and ecological problems related to 30 years
of nuclear testing in French Polynesia;<P>

- transparency in the documentation of the French nuclear testing
program and free access  to information concerning the risks of
these tests for the Maohi's and the workers at Mururoa and
Fangatoufa, in order to stop the lies of the French State which
encroach upon human rights.<P>

     In order to enforce these demands we call for:<P>

- an international boycott of French products and services;<P>

- a boycott of the Pacific Ocean Games.<P>

We strongly encourage all similar non-violent initiatives.<P>

     Some nations (the inhabitants of the Marshall-islands, the
Aboriginals of Australia) succeeded in their struggle and
received compensation for the criminally irresponsible nuclear
tests on their territory. The French nuclear bombs are just as
dangerous and the persons responsible know this very well, yet
they continue to terrorise Polynesia with their nuclear program!<P>

     In our Maohi tradition when a child is born, we bury the
placenta in the ground in order to connect the child with the
nourishing Earth. At the place where the placenta is buried,  we
plant a fruittree, most often an uru (a typical and legendary
bread-tree of Tahiti. This is a symbolic expression of Life. 
Thus starting at birth everybody is closely connected with
Nature.<P>

     Ours is a struggle for Life, rather than a race towards
Nuclear Death. France has injured us in our deepest self by
planting a bomb in the belly of Mururoa and Fangatoufa. She has
seriously contaminated the mother that feeds our children and
grandchildren. This is a crime against future generations. We are
not in need of any kind of justification for resisting this
killing madness. <P>

     For the whole planet, we shall all cry out together so
loudly against this scandalous act that even a deaf man like
French President Jacques Chirac will no longer be able to ignore
our voices.<P>

We are sure that all together, in the House of Peace that we have
built, hand in hand, we will find the solutions to save our lands
and the whole world. <P>

     Our organisation is called "HITI TAU" which means in Maohi
" the time to act has come" :<P>

<B>LET'S ACT ALL TOGETHER <BR>
TO HAVE NUCLEAR WEAPONS BE DECLARED ILLEGAL</B><P>

</DL>
<HR>
</TD></TABLE>
