<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Boycott French Products - PRESS RELEASE - </TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<A HREF=boyidx.html><IMG SRC=/~fme/images/boycott.gif BORDER=0 ALT=Back to boycott index></A>
<HR>
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>

<TABLE BORDER=1><TR>
<TD WIDTH=140 VALIGN=TOP><CENTER><FONT SIZE=-1>
<IMG SRC=/~fme/images/fme-logo.gif ALT="For Mother Earth" ALIGN=CENTER HSIZE=133 VSIZE=111 BORDER=0>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1><P> <P>PRESS<BR>RELEASE<P><HR><p></font><FONT SIZE=-1>
<A HREF=/~fme/contact.html>Contact address:</a>
<P>Gewad 15<BR>9000 Gent, Belgium<BR>Phone +32-9-2334924<BR>Fax: +32-9-2337802<BR>
Email: <A HREF="mailto:boycott@motherearth.knooppunt.be">click here</A><BR>
<P></FONT></TD><TD WIDHT=700 VALIGN=TOP>

<DL><DL>
<H1>Fourth French Nuketest this year</H1>

France went ahead with the fourth nuketest this year, at 22:30
local Belgian time at the atoll of Mururoa according to the newsagency
Belga. The test had a yield of 40 kiloton, twice Hiroshima!!<P>

France's determination to stick with the testing created a rift in the 
European Union last week after most EUropean Nations voted for a UN resolution
condemning the tests. The resolution was approved by 95 countries.
France and Britain were the only European Union members voting against
the resolution. The USA abstained, aswell as all former Eastern European
countries.<P>

Chirac canceled the annual French-Italian summit scheduled for Naples
on Nov. 24-25, aswell as with Belgian Prime-Minister. He thanked Germany, 
Spain and Greece for abstaining on the vote and praised them for
what he called their 'attitude of solidarity'.<P>
  
<H2>ACTION</H2>

It is clear that FOR MOTHER EARTH will again show solidarity with
the Indigenous People. We continue to network the call of the Maohi
to boycott French products, and have nuclear weapons declared illegal.<P>

Today, at noon we will again join the vigil of the Belgian Teststop 
coalition in front of the French embassy in Brussels. We have a
national meeting scheduled later in the afternoon. Further we
are preparing a 'surprise action' for December together with
the Flemish branch of War Resistors International. Look out for the
news!!<P>

<H2>PLEASE LET US KNOW WHAT YOU WILL DO WITH YOUR GROUP</H2>
  
<H3>NUCLEAR WEAPONS ARE IN VIOLATION WITH INTERNATIONAL LAW</H3>

Further we started using the 'Public Declaration of Conscience',
in support of the World Court Project, to have nuclear weapons being
declared illegal by the International Court of Justice (ICJ).<P>

Over 3.000.000 signatures were already gathered worldwide by a growing
network of groups who understand the significance of what grew in a
few years as the largest case before the ICJ. <P>

We were at a seminar in Den Haag (NL)  lately and grabbed the 
importance of this courtcase aswell. We will sent you more
info soon. <P>

Last Saturday the first 1.000 signatures were collected in Gent. 
The plan is to gather many thousands before the end of the year, as
the court is expected to give its opinion in january or february!!<P>

<CENTER><B><BLINK>YOU CAN HELP!!</BLINK></B></CENTER>

</DL>
</TD></TABLE>
