<PRE>
 Ten years after cherNObyl

 Walk for a Nuclear-Free Future  
 Ukraine April 12-26 1996

 Gent, April 6th 1996 -  FOR MOTHER EARTH activists from Austria,
 Belarus, Belgium, Canada, Finland, Germany, Netherlands, Rumania,
 Russia, Slovakia, Sri Lanka, Turkey and the Ukraine are
 expected on April 12th in Kiev to prepare for a commemorative
 anti-nuclear walk to mark the tenth anniversary of the Chernobyl
 nuclear disaster of April 26th 1986. 

 The 'Walk for a Nuclear-Free Future' starts on April 17th in Kiev
 with a ceremony and action, and ends at the 30km zone near the
 Chernobyl NPP next April 26th 1996, exactly ten years after the
 nuclear explosion of reactor 4. 

 The walk is organised in partnership with the Union of Salvation of
 Chernobyls, a Ukrainian NGO which is active in citizens network for
 radiation-monitoring in inhabited contaminated areas. 

 The walk is designed to draw attention for the victims of  the
 disaster and denounce the ongoing false promises and lies of the
 nuclear industry. The organizers demand a complete phase-out of all
 NPP's and promotion of energy-saving programs and renewable energies.
 FOR MOTHER EARTH states that we have to stop the nuclear
 contamination at its source : the mining of uranium. 

 The walk will start in Kiev, after work-shops and an official visit
 to the infamous nuclear power plant where two reactors are still
 operational. The walk will cover 25km/day in the north-western region
 of Kiev. A ceremony and a non-violent action is planned on April
 26th. 

 The walkers will be confronted directly with the aftermath of the 
 Chernobyl disaster as they will meet liquidators, medicals, people
 who were forced to relocate, or who received no support to move,
 ... human-faces whose stories will illustrate the enormous
 consequences of the largest industrial accident. A recent United
 Nations report on Chernobyl states 9 million people were affected
 by the Chernobyl catastrophe, and this only in the Ukraine, Belarus
 and Russia. 

 In this year, marking the tenth anniversary of the Chernobyl
 disaster, FOR MOTHER EARTH launched an international petition to
 demand the reform of the UN International Atomic Energy Agency
 (IAEA). The ecological group demands the stop of the promotion of
 nuclear power by this UN agency, and the creation of a UN Energy
 Agency to encourage research and promote energy savings and
 renewable energies. This campaign receives already support from
 Greenpeace International and 'Abolition 2000' a global large
 network of over 300 NGO's. 

 FOR MOTHER EARTH is an international anti-nuclear citizens network. 
 There are now groups in Belarus, Belgium, Germany, Netherlands,
 Slovakia and the USA. FOR MOTHER EARTH organised succesfully two
 5.500km cross-continental anti- nuclear walks in 1992 (USA) and
 1995 (Europe). 

<HR>

 Media-advisory - Ten years after cherNObyl

 Walk for a Nuclear-Free Future 
 Ukraine April 12-26 1996

        **!!!!!Note for photographers/camera(wo)men!!!!!**

 Strongest photo-opportunities are marked with >*****<


 April 12th      International meeting FOR MOTHER EARTH

 April 13th      Welcoming walk participants
                 Welcoming party

 April 14th      Work-shops on Chernobyl NPP and alternatives to
                 nuclear power 

 April 15th      Visit to Chernobyl NPP

 April 16th      Non-violence training and last practical
                 preparations 

 April 17th      START WALK with ceremony and action in Kiev>*****<
                 Walkers will have signs with names 76      >*****< 
                 Ukrainian villages which were evacuated    >*****<
                 Take train to Korostin (N-W of Kiev)

 The walk will cover aprox. 25km/day, and go through
 inhabited low-level contaminated areas south-west of Chernobyl NPP.
 The walkers will wear white radiation-suits and have dust masks
 for protection. The Union of Salvation of Chernobyls
 prepares activities with local population along the route.

 April 18th      Walk Korostin - Ignatpol

 April 19th      Walk Ignatpol - Ovruch

 April 20th      Walk Ovruch - Narodichi

 April 21st      Restday and action prep. April 26!

 April 22nd      Walk Narodichi - Paleskoye

 April 23th      Walk Paleskoye - Kraciatichi

 April 24th      Walk Kraciatichi - Ivankov

 April 25th      Walk Ivankov - Aranaye

 April 26th      MIDNIGHT WALK TO 30km-zone with torches   >******<
                 Ceremony at 1:23 a.m. (time zero in 1986) >******<
                 Visual Non-violent actions                >******<
                 (under press-embargo till April 26!)

 April 27th      Human-chain in Kiev
                 Anti-nuclear music gathering with Ukranian bands

