<html>
<HEAD><TITLE>General Information about the Walk Across Europe</TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="waeidx.html"><IMG SRC="../images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A>
<A HREF=wrepovv.html><IMG SRC=../images/actreprt.gif ALT="Action Reports"></a><hr>

<h2>An introduction to the Walk Across Europe for a Nuclear-free World 1995 </h1>
<font size=-2><CENTER><B>BRUSSELS - LONDON - NIJMEGEN - FRANKFURT - PRAHA - WIEN - KIEV - CHERNOBYL - MINSK - MOSCOW </B></center></FONT><P>

<IMG SRC=../images/walk3mon.gif ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=15 VSPACE=10>

<em>For Mother Earth</em> is an independant non-profit grassroots organization which organizes initiatives to promote human rights, disarmament and protection of the natural environment.<p>
Direct-democracy based on consensus-decision making, and non-violent conflict-resolution are important political choices in our path to reach these goals.<p>
<em>For Mother Earth</em> was founded in 1991. In 1992 we organized a 5.500 km <A HREF=../waa/waaidx.html>Walk across America</a> in Solidarity with Native Americans and for an immediate halt of nuclear testing. An average of 100 people walked from New York City to the Nevada Test Site linking the violation of Indigenous Peoples' landrights and nuclear developments worldwide.<p>

<h3><i>Everybody wants to get back to nature, but not by foot</i></h3>

For Mother Earth believes that walking is an efficient way to campaign at a time where the survival of all life is endangered. Next to letter-writing campaigns, organizing, speaking, petitioning, non-violent direct actions of civil disobedience....<b>we walk!</b> For Mother Earth is walking in a strong way! Will we walk alone? Or will you walk with us? Together we can walk for a difference!<p>

For Mother Earth designed the Walk Across Europe for a Nuclear-free World 1995 as part of its ongoing international anti-nuclear campaign. The walk will call attention to the social, environmental and economical consequences of the Atomic Age and give concrete examples of alternatives.<p>

<em>The objective of a nuclear-free World </em> will be met not only through walking but with an <A HREF=petition.html>international petition</a>, street theatre, symbolic actions and non-violent direct actions. We realize that the present situation calls for our walking to not only be on the streets, but tresspassing nuclear site ares, into government officials' offices and into jails if necessary.<p>

The <em>Walk Across Europe</em> for a Nuclear-Free World started in Brussels on January 12th 1995, an will end in Moscow October 12th 1995, the International Day of Solidarity with Indigenous People. The route started in Belgium, passed through France, England and the Netherlands, and passes Germany, Czech Republic, Austria, Slovakia, Ukraine, Belarus and ends in Russia. The Walk will visit the five European nuclear weapon states, the Wien headquarters of the International Atomic Energy Agency, Chernobyl, the worst human-made accident ever, and numerous civilian and military nuclear facilities.<p>

<UL>
  <li><A HREF=route.html>The route: 5.500 km from Brussels to Moscow</a> <A HREF=routemap.html>14 Kb Route Map)</a>
  <li><A HREF=petition.html>The Statement of Purpose</a>
</ul>

<hr>
<address><font size=-2>&copy '94/'95 For Mother Earth International, Gent, Belgium</address>
</body>
</html>       

