<HEAD><TITLE>Statement of Purpose</TITLE></HEAD>
<body>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A>
<A HREF="reports/wrepovv.html"><IMG SRC="../images/actreprt.gif" ALT="Action Reports"></a><hr>

<center><h1>The Statement of Purpose</h1></center>

<BR><FONT size=+1><B><UL>
  <LI>Stop the 'Atomic Age'
  <LI>Start Renewable Energy for the Future
</ul></b></font>

<BR><I><B>We the undersigned support FOR MOTHER EARTH's Walk across
Europe for a Nuclear-Free World 1995, and demand that the
world's political leaders immediately implement the following:</B></I><p>

<BR><H2>Stop</H2>
<UL>
<LI>all nuclear testing immediately
<LI>the mining of uranium
<LI>the use of Indigenous People's lands for nuclear activities
<LI>the production of nuclear weapons
<LI>stop the Western Nuclear Lobby going East and phase out all nuclear power plants immediately
<LI>the production of all additional nuclear waste (in accordance with the phase-out plan) and halt nuclear fuel reprocessing immediately
<LI>the promotional and technological functions of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA)
</UL><p>

<BR><H2>Start</H2>
<UL>
<LI>the funding of a health and housing programme for those affected by  nuclear testing in the past
<LI>funding for correcting its environmental impact
<LI>immediate negotiations with the traditional councils for compensating aboriginal landclaims
<LI>a peacefund for research and training on nonviolence & destroy existing nuclear weapons as they are in violation with International law. Treat nuclear warheads as waste
<LI>funding the use of alternative energy sources while implementing programmes energy efficiency/savings, and job conversions
<LI>redirecting nuclear expertise and funding to the finding of short and long term solutions to the problem of waste. In interim, store waste in above ground retrievable storage near existing nuclear facilities
<LI>using the IAEA as a purely nuclear control organization that gives Non Governmental Organizations participation in policy-making and create a new international Energy Agency under United Nations for research and promotion of renewable energy
</UL>

<hr>
<address><font size=-2>&copy '94/'95 For Mother Earth, Gent, Belgium</address>
</body>
</html>
</DOC>
