<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Indignenous Peoples Uranium Speaking tour in Europe</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>

<H1>
 <IMG SRC=../images/walkura.gif ALT="" BORDER=0>
 Indigenous Peoples Uranium Speaking tour in Europe - fall 1997
</H1>

<H2>More about the Uranium Speaking Tour</H3>

<H3>Why?</H3>

<P>FOR MOTHER EARTH plans to invite Indigenous Peoples'
representatives from several continents to share their experience
with uranium mining companies destroying their lives and land to
meet the demands for nuclear fuel in industrialized nations. </P>

<P>With this speaking tour FOR MOTHER EARTH wants to inform the
public about the first step in the nuclear chain - and the
negative consequences for people and the environment.</P>

<P>Nuclear testing programs have learned us that the nuclear
industry, and its economical, financial, military and political
allies, have shown no concerns about sacrifying the sacred lands
of Indigenous People for their nuclear experiments (i.e. Maohi,
Western Shoshone Indians, Australian Aboriginals, Kazahk, Nenets,
...)</P>

<P>FOR MOTHER EARTH wants to continue to support Indigenous Peoples
struggle for self-determination, expose and oppose the racist
policies of the nuclear industry. </P>

<P>With this tour FOR MOTHER EARTH wants to inform and encourage
citizens groups to demand a halt of nuclear contamination and
colonialism at its source : the mining of uranium. With this
European tour we want to create new links and strenghten a
anti-uranium mining network. </P>

<H3>Who?</H3>

<P>Indigenous Peoples representatives from:</P> 

<PRE>
	Australia      => Northern Territories  => FoE Sydney and Fitzroy

	Asia           => ????                  => ???

	Africa         => Niger?                => Thomas Siepelmeyer ?
	
	South-America  => ????                  => ???

	North-America  => Saskatchewan (Canada) => ICUC 

               => Man-Walking-Stick Alone (USA) will also be on
               the tour. He will add music, as he is a
               traditional flute-builder and -player. He also
               knows a lot about u-mining and renewables.

	Europe      => Peter Diehl ?
	            => one or two FME tour coordinators
</PRE>

<H3>When?</H3>

<P>The tour will start on October 10th 1997 in Belgium, and travel
for 6 to 8 weeks around Europe. It will end in Brussels for 
evaluation and planning.</P>

<H3>Where?</H3>

<P>The tour will travel first through Western Europe, to move
through Central Europe to Eastern Europe</P>

<P>We have already received interest for hosting the tour in :</P>

<PRE>

	West      => France, Italy, Denmark, Germany, Finland and Sweden
             
	Central   => Slovakia and Rumania  

	East      => Belarus and Ukraine
</PRE>

<P>These are all Indigenous People Support groups or FME groups. In
november a mailing will go out to anti-nuclear groups in Europe.</P>

<P>A final schedule of the tour should be made in summer 1997. 
Selection will be made according to practical, political and
financial means. </P>

<H3>What?</H3>

<P>The tour organisers from Belgium sugggest following ingredients:
press-conference, meeting with politicians, public and nuclear
industry, media-genic non-violent actions and benefits.</P>

<P>In Belgium we will be looking to following proposal during our next
meeting:</P>

<PRE>
	Wednesday October 8th - Brussel
	=> Arrival and welcoming participants

	Thursday October 9th - Brussels
	=> Tour briefing and rest

	Friday October 10th - Brussels
	=> Simultanous press-conference, non-violent action and meeting
   	   at Synatom, the Belgian company which purchases uranium.

	Saturday October 11th - Gent
	=> Information event (afternoon) & benefit party with concert
	   (evening - night)

	Sunday October 12th - Gent, Leuven or Antwerp???
	=> Rest and/or another info-event in i.e. Antwerp or Leuven

	Monday October 13th - Brussels
	=> Meeting with national and European Union politicians

	Tuesday October 14th - ???????
	=> Leave for ??
<PRE>

<H3>Work and rest</H3>

<P>The tour should be slow to start. We wish to take it easy after
the participants long travels, aswell as take enough time for
informing the delegates for the long and intense journey ahead. 
There should be enough time for rest and sightseeing during the
'entire' tour.</P>

<H3>Non-violent actions</H3>

<P>We will stress the importance of creative non-violent actions to
other organisers. We learned that without such actions => no
media => new info to same small circle of people.</P>

<P>Indigenous People will be the main spokespeople towards media
during such actions. They will not participate actively in
actions (to avoid their arrests), unless they choose to.</P>

<H3>Other good to knows</H3>

<H4>Air fares</H4>

<P>FME will raise funds to pay for the airfares of the Indigenous
People. Suggestions for donors are welcome.</P>

<H4>Transport in Europe</H4>

<P>Hostcountries will provide funds and/or means of transport to and
within their country. I.e. if tour goes from Belgium to France:
French organisers pay way to and within France. And so on.</P>

<H4>Food and accomodation</H4>

<P>Hostcountries will provide food and accomodation. Special
requests for food should be communicated to FME. We suggest the
particpants to be welcomed at private homes, to avoid hotel
expenses.</P>

<B><P>Contact</P></B>
Pol D'Huyvetter, For Mother Earth International 
<BR>E-mail: <A HREF=mailto:int@fme.knooppunt.be>int@fme.knooppunt.be</A><B></P>


