<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Indignenous Peoples Uranium Speaking tour in Europe</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>

<H1>
 <IMG SRC=../images/walkura.gif ALT="" BORDER=0>
 Indigenous Peoples Uranium Speaking tour in Europe - fall 1997
</H1>

<H3>URANIUM VS INDIGENOUS PEOPLES - Introduction</H3>

<P>The Indigenous Peoples Support Group of For Mother Earth in Belgium
decided to work with priority on gathering information on the issue
of uranium mining vs. Indigenous People.</P>

<P>As we all know, uranium was and is the fuel for nuclear testing,
nuclear bombs and atomic power. It is portrayed by the nuclear
industry and governments as necessary for our security and welfare.</P>

<P>However, we have learned that uranium is a deadly metal : the first
step in an evil nuclear chain. Few people have received
comprehensive information on the issue of uranium mining. And even
fewer people know about the consequences of u-mining for Indigenous
People around the globe. </P>

<P>To make a difference we plan to:</P>  

<UL>
 <LI><P>Publicise a book (or brochure) in summer 1997 gathering
  comprehensive information on uranium mining activities around the
  world vs. Indigenous People, and deepen the work that was started
  on this issue by the organisers of the World Uranium Hearing in
  1992.</P>
 
  <P>An introduction should give the reader insight on uranium mining,
  its place in the nuclear cycle, the effects on environment and
  health, and give intro on the global uranium market (supply and
  demand). </P>

  <P>In seperate chapters, we wish to have a closer look to
  uranium mining on different continents, and gather facts on the
  many cases of opposition by the traditional caretakers of the land,
  the Indigenous Peoples. </P>

  <P>We are looking for guestwriters to make this book happen. Hopefully
  we will find many local people who wish to contribute.</P> 

  <P><A HREF="mailto: int@fme@knooppunt.be">Please feel invited to contribute, or make suggestions!!</A></P>

 <LI><P> Organise a European Indigenous Peoples Uranium Speaking Tour in
  fall 1997. Purpose is to hear the testimony of Indigenous Peoples'
  representatives on the land-rights violations, the destruction of the
  environment and the danger for health. We wish to confront their
  experiences and views with the European demand for nuclear fuel for
  nuclear power generation. We already received positive responses
  for cooperation from i.e. Germany, Italy, Denmark, Finland, while
  For Mother Earth activists in different Western, Central and
  Eastern European countries agreed to be part of organising this
  tour.</P>
  
 <LI><P> And finally, after the tour, we could compile and produce a video
  documentary, hopefully broad-cast quality.</P>
</UL>

<P>Yes, an ambitious project.</P>

<P>My first job has consisted in looking for contacts. And I feel
thankful for the many people who have shown genuine interest for
these projects. From others I received the names and accounts
(mostly through Peter Diehl and LAKA) as potentially interested
people.</P>

<B><P>Contact</P></B>
Pol D'Huyvetter, For Mother Earth International 
<BR>E-mail: <A HREF=mailto:int@fme.knooppunt.be>int@fme.knooppunt.be</A><B></P>

