<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>For Mother Earth - USA Office</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<H1><IMG SRC=../images/officeus.gif HEIGHT=50 WIDTH=50 ALT=""> USA Office</H1>

<P>The Community Organizing Center/For Mother Earth office has 
four main tracks for which we organize:</P>

<LI>Develop a network for Economic and Environmental Justice; 
in this work, we include the relationship with For Mother Earth, 
our support of efforts to stop Radwaste storage and transportation,
our organizing of organizations whose main work is environment and 
plunge them into economic and environmental discussions to develop 
working relationships toward economic and environmental justice, and
starting to work on a countywide recycling program for Franklin 
County, (among other things).</LI>
<P></P>
<LI>Establish the Ohio-Cuba Action Group; where we implement 
scholarly exchanges with Ohio based institutions of higher 
education and Cuban based, as well as sending delegations 
to Cuba for priliminary visits.</LI>
<P></P>
<LI>Initiate Congregation-Based Community Organizing; which has
planned a founding convention for September for the Columbus Organizing 
Project (which is an organization of congregatons that will seek 
to be the moral barometer of Columbus). AND</LI>
<P></P>
<LI>Plan annual Indigenous Peoples Observations; where our work 
with Leonard Peltier defense and other pressing Native American
issues take place, and each October plan public events to 
counterbalance the  hysteria of Columbus discovery/invasion
with the view of those from the shore not the ship.</LI>  

<P>We are also supporting efforts in organization: The Ohio 
Empowerment Coalition - welfare/poverty persons led organizing, 
and a network for an alternative agenda - that seeks to influence 
the 1996 national/local elections.  This office is busy doing 
alternative to violence programmatic efforts as well.  Basically, 
the Community Organizing Center seeks to make Columbus a 
community, our motto.  There is more but that is enough.</P>

<B><P>More info? Email: <A HREF=mailto:walk@igc.apc.org>walk@igc.apc.org</A></P></B>

<P>
<A HREF=../index.html><IMG SRC=../images/home.gif ALT="Back to Homepage" BORDER=0></A><BR>
