<HEAD><TITLE> Walk action report 1 - Brussels	</TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/waeidx.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~fme/images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A>
<A HREF=wrep001b.html><IMG SRC = "/~fme/images/arrwriht.gif"></A>

<H2>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</H2>
<H2>Brussels, Thursday January 12th 1995
  </H2>


<HR>
<H1>5.500 km walk starts in Brussels<BR>
THE FIRST STEPS TOWARDS A NUCLEAR FREE WORLD
 </H1>

<P>
<B>Over a 150 people made the first steps of a 5.500 kilometer
long Walk across Europe for a Nuclear-Free World to Moscow.
The Walk is organized by the international organisation FOR MOTHER
EARTH.	The walk will end at the Kremlin in Moscow on October
12th 1995, the International Day of Solidarity with Indigenous
People. Indigenous People suffer a lot from nuclear testing,
uranium mining anbd nuclear waste.
</B><P>
The walkers demand a complete halt of nuclear testing, the
outlaw of nuclear weapons, the review and extension of the
Non-Proliferation Treaty, the phase-out of nuclear power and
use of renewable energies.
<P>
This morning walkers from Austria, Belarus, Belgium, Bulgaria,
Canada, England, France, Germany, the Indian Blackfeet Nation,
Rumania and the USA gathered in the Jubelpark for the opening
ceremony. Two American Indians gave the walkers a
eaglefeathers; symbols for protection in the American Indian
culture. The ceremony was followed with in 'die in' in front
of the buildings of the European Commission. With the banner :
'Nuclear energy goes over dead bodies' they wanted to show
that Europe is also responsable for the nuclearization of the
planet which endangers humanity and the environment.
<P>
An exhibition trailer on renewable energy  and
energy-efficincy will travel along with the Walk across
Europe for a Nuclear Free World. This Sustainable Energy Tour,
organized by SNORE (Sustainable Network on Renewable Energy),
is equiped with solarcollectors and a windturbine.
<P>
During this nine month journey the walkers will cross France,
England, Flanders, the Netherlands, Germany, Czech Republic,
Austria, Slovakia, Ukraine and Belarus. The walkers will
commemorate fifty years Hiroshima on August 6, 1995 at the NPP
of Chernobyl.

			     -end-


<P>
<HR>
For more information, registrations and financial support:

<address>

FOR MOTHER EARTH International, Gent Belgium<BR>

</address><A HREF=/~fme/wae/waeidx.html>[INDEX]</A> <A HREF=wrep001b.html>[NEXT]</A>
</body></html>
