<HEAD><TITLE>Walk action report 2 - SHAPE & Mons </TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/waeidx.html"><IMG SRC = "/~fme/images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A> <A HREF="/~walk/contacta.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~walk/images/contacta.gif" ALT="Contact Addresses"></A> <A HREF=wrep001c.html><IMG SRC = "arrwleft.gif"></A><A HREF="wrepovv.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~walk/images/actreprt.gif"  ALT="Action Report" ></A><A HREF=wrep003.html><IMG SRC = "/~walk/images/arrwriht.gif"></A>

<H2>for immediate release</H2>
<H2>Mons, January 15th 1995   </H2>


<HR>
<H1>Walkers call for SHAPE to respect Indigenous Rights
 </H1>

<P>
<B>
Last saturday, seventy members of the 5,500 km Walk Across
Europe for a Nuclear Free World, halted at the main gate of
the Supreme Headquarters of the Allied Powers in Europe
(SHAPE). SHAPE is the military think-tank of the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), near Mons in the South of
Belgium.
</B><P>
After a peaceful demonstration the walkers met with  Major
Boulanger, a Belgian public information officer for SHAPE.
<P>
According to Pol D'Huyvetter, spokesperson for the walkers,
NATO has blocked since the 1960's all resolutions within the
UN  General Assembly for complete nuclear disarmament.
"Indigenous peoples worldwide have suffered enormously because
of the nuclear deterrent policy of NATO", he said, and
stressed "that NATO disregarded Indigenous People's landrights
in their nuclear programmes".
<P>
According to the walkers France has tested their nuclear
weapons on the territory of the Tuareg in North Africa, and
the Maohi in Polynesia. The UK tested their atomic bombs on
lands of the Aboriginals, and the Shoshone American Indians in
Nevada. The USA have tested over 800 nuclear weapons in Nevada
since 1951. They also tested their weapons on the lands of the
Mescalero Apaches in New Mexico, the Inuits in Alaska, and the
Marshall Islanders at the Bikini Atoll in the Pacific.

<P>The walkers demanded that Major Boulanger informs the British,
French and US officials at SHAPE of the violation of the
landrights of Indigenous Peoples. They urged the NATO
officials to agree to an immediate halt to nuclear testing
(CTBT) at the UN Geneva Conference of Disarmament.
<P>
After their stop at the SHAPE HQ, the walkers headed for the
city of Mons, where they took part in a ceremony at the
Hibakusha Park at the University.
Hibakusha is a Japanese word for the victims of Hiroshima and
Nagasaki.
The ceremony was lead by Skyhawk, a Blackfeet Native American
and Laura Johnson, a mixed blood American of Blackfoot
Hungarian ancestor. Prayers were shared for all victims of the
nuclear age. Prof. Pierre Pierart has planted a tree with a
memorial stone for every nuclear test since 1988.
<P>
On Sunday the walkers crossed the French border on their way
to Paris, where they plan to arrive on Jan 27th. The walkers
should arrive in Moscow on Oct 12th 1995, the International
Day of Solidarity with Indigenous People.
<P>
With this walk, FOR MOTHER EARTH, the international organising
group, calls for a immediate halt of nuclear testing, complete
nuclear disarmament and the review and renewal of the
Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT). The NPT Review Conference
takes place in New York next April.
The walkers urge a complete phase out of Nuclear power,
through energy efficiency programmes and the development of
sustainable energy. A Danish semi-truck, with an exhibition on
sustainable energy travels along with the walkers.
<P>
After France the walkers will march through England, the
Netherlands, Germany, Czech Republic, Austria, Slovakia,
Ukraine, Belarus and Russia.
<P>
The walk participants come from Austria, Belarus, Belgium, the
Blackfoot Nation, Bulgaria, Canada, Denmark, England, France,
the Netherlands, Rumania, Urkaine and the USA.
The organizers say to expect more participants to join the
walk, including representatives from the Czech Republic,
Germany, Japan, Slovakia, Sri Lanka, Russia and Turkey.
<P>
They will commemorate the 50th anniversary of Hiroshima near
the Chernobyl nuclear power plant, and will cross the
Belarussian border on Nagasaki-Day, August 9th.
<P>
			     -end-


<P>
<HR>
For more information, registrations and financial support:

<address> FOR MOTHER EARTH International, Gent, Belgium
</address><A HREF=/~fme/wae/waeidx.html>[INDEX]</A> <A HREF=wrep003.html>[NEXT]</A>

</body>
