<HEAD><TITLE>Walk action report 3 - Taverny and Paris </TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/waeidx.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~fme/images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A>
<A HREF="wrepovv.html"><IMG SRC  = "actreprt.gif"  ALT="Action Report" ></A>
<A HREF=wrep004.html><IMG SRC = "arrwriht.gif"></A>

<H2>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</H2>
<H2>Taverny-Paris, January 26th 1995  </H2>


<HR>
<H1>Anti-nuke walkers demonstrate at french nuclear Headquarter of
Taverny / L'Elysee receives a delegation of the walkers </H1>
<H3>
Action in Taverny</H3>
<P>
<B>Thursday, seventy participants of the 5,500 km Walk Across Europe
for a Nuclear Free World, organised an one hour visual non-
violent action - with support of French peace and environmental
groups - at the main entrance of the French Operational Center
of Strategic Airforces (COFAS 1) in Taverny, the largest military
nuclear HQ in France. They walked in a silent row towards to the
base dressed in white radiationsuits and carrying boards with the
names of all indigenous tribes who suffered from nuclear testing
programmes. The walkers carried also banners expressing their
demands. At the base a vigil took place as well as a
streettheatre play. A delegation of the walkers met with Colonel
Luc Robin, commander of the military base, in order to emphasize
the destructive nuclear role of France in the international
community.
</B><P>

During the action there was also an Indian ceremony, lead by
Skyhawk, a Blackfeet American Indian. Prayers were shared for all
victims of the nuclear age and especially for many Indigenous
People who have been affected by nuclear developments, i.e.
uranium mining, nuclear testing and rad-waste. Many tribes of
indigenous people suffered from the nuclear program of French
Compagnies (Cogema, Somair, Minatom,...),for example Touaregs in
Niger and Algeria, the Maohi in Polynesia, the Wollaston Chipewyan
people in Saskatchewan, etc).<P>

<H3>Meeting at L'Elysee </H3>

A delegation of the walkers: (Pol D'Huyvetter (Bel) -FOR MOTHER
EARTH International-; Perline(F) - Groupement des Scientifiques
pour l'information sur les Energies Nucleaires- and Solange
Fernex (F) - Women for Peace) has been received at 16.30 hr. by Jean
Levy, a Diplomatic Advisor of President Mitterand at l'Elysee in
Paris. The delegation asked the Advisor to present their demands
to the President, emphasizing to stop nuclear testing (CTBT) and
a review of the Non-Proliferation Treaty. The walk will do a
follow-up on the nuclear policy of France.
At 14.00 hr. there was also a gathering of the European Ministers
of Justice in Paris; for the walkers a moment to highlight that
the use and threat to use nuclear weapons are illegal.
<P>
<H3>Walkers will arrive in Paris </H3>
On Friday January 27th the walkers will arrive in Paris. The next
day - Saturday - they will participate in a manifestation at the
'Parvis de Beaubourg' from 17.00 hr. to 19.00 hr.
<P>
The 'Walk across Europe for a nuclear-free world 1995' demands
a halt of nuclear testing, a review of the Non-Proliferation
Treaty, the phase-out of nuclear power and the development of
sustainable energy.They also want to pay attention to the fate
of indigenous people(see above)
<P>
A Danish truck with a 50 m2 mobile exhibition on energy saving
and renewable energy is travelling along with the walkers to
Moscow. On January 25th and 26th it will be in the Place Charles
de Gaulle in Taverny. On January 27th-28th-29th it will be in the
Place de la Republique in Paris.
<P>
After Paris the walkers will continue their way through l'Eure
and Calvados up to Cherbourg (February 15th and 16th) and finally
head to England, the Netherlands, Germany, Czech Republic,
Austria, Slovakia, Ukraine, Belarus and Russia.
<P>
The walk participants come from Austria, Belarus, Belgium, the
Blackfoot Nation, Bulgaria, Canada, Denmark, England, France, the
Netherlands, Rumania, Ukraine and the USA.
<P>
			    - end -

<P>
<HR>
For more information, registrations and financial support:

<address>
FOR MOTHER EARTH International, Gent, Belgium
</address><A HREF=/~fme/wae/waeidx.html>[INDEX]</A> <A HREF=wrep004.html>[NEXT]</A>

