<HEAD><TITLE> Walk action report 4 - Saclay   </TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/waeidx.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~fme/images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A>

<H2>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</H2>
<H2>Saclay, January 30th 1995  </H2>


<HR>
<H1>Walkers block Nuclear Study Center of Saclay near Paris
 </H1>

<P>
<B>Twenty five walkers dressed in white radiation-suits started a
non-violent blockade at 9.15 am this morning of the main en-
trance of the Nuclear Study Center of Saclay. The walkers
expressed their opposiation against the military and civil
research done in the Saclay Center. On a large banner the
workers could read "Non a la proliferation nucleaire".
The walkers stopped their symbolic blockade after 25 minutes,
and contineud their 25 km daily walk.
The walkers coming from 13 different countries are now on
their way to the Cherbourg - La Hague region.

			     -end-

</B>
<P>
<HR>
For more information, registrations and financial support:

