<HEAD><TITLE> Walk action report 6 - Cherbourg	 </TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/waeidx.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~fme/images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A>

<H2>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</H2>
<H2>Cherbourg, February 14th 1995 </H2>


<HR>
<H1>Walkers block main entrance of nuclear submarine base </H1>

<P>
<B>Sixty participants in the Walk across Europe for a Nuclear
Free World arrived this afternoon in Cherbourg. After their
daily 25km the walkers ended their walk before the main en-
trance of l'Arsenal with a 'die in'.
</B><P>


The Arsenal is an important French military harbor and it is
the place where France has its shipyard for the construction
of nuclear submarines for its 'Force de Frappe' (nuclear
deterrent).
<P>
The walkers blocked the main gate from 5 to 5.30pm, the
closing time where all the workers leave their job. It was the
first time in its history that the Arsenal was blocked.
There were no arrest nor incidents.

<P>
<HR>
For more information, registrations and financial support:

<address>
FOR MOTHER EARTH International, Gent, Belgium

</address><A HREF=/~fme/wae/waeidx.html>[INDEX]</A> <A HREF=wrep007.html>[NEXT]</A>

</body>
</html>






