<HEAD><TITLE>Walk action report 8 - Cherbourg	</TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/index.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~fme/images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A> <A HREF="/~walk/contacta.html"><IMG SRC  = "contacta.gif" ALT="Contact Addresses"></A> <A HREF=wrep007.html><IMG SRC = "arrwleft.gif"></A><A HREF="wrepovv.html"><IMG SRC  = "actreprt.gif"  ALT="Action Report" ></A><A HREF=wrep009.html><IMG SRC = "arrwriht.gif"></A>

<H2>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</H2>
<H2>Cherbourg, February 16th 1995
 </H2>


<HR>
<H1>ANTI-NUKE WALKERS OCCUPY CRANE OF COGEMA IN CHERBOURG
 </H1>

<P>
<B>Thursday February 16th at 9 am, 12 members of the international
organization FOR MOTHER EARTH have penetrated Cogema's site at
the harbour of Cherbourg. Taken by surprise, the security-guards
were not able to stop the anti-nuke activist from occupying the
Cogema's crane in the harbour of Cherbourg. Ten activists have
locked themselves to the crane and the fence.
</B><P>


We just learned that the activists stopped their symbolic
occupation at 12h20.
<P>
The Cogema crane is needed for the sea-transport of plutonium and
nuclear waste from and to Japan. Very soon this crane will be
used to load a boat with highly radioactive waste which will be
sent Japan. Out of confidential sources FOR MOTHER EARTH learned
this transport will take place next Thuesday.
<P>
The FOR MOTHER EARTH-activist denounce that nuclear transports,
by any means, i.e. by boats, planes, trucks or trains, are very
dangerous for the environment and the public health. According
to the organization, the only way to end these transports is to
forbid the separating of plutonium from nuclear waste. FOR MOTHER
EARTH demands a halt on the reprocessing of nuclear waste
originating from Belgium, Germany, Holland, Switzerland and Japan
at La Hague. There are activists from Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria,
Blackfeet Indian Nation, Canada, Denmark, France, Germany, the
Netherlands, Rumania, Switzerland, Ukraine and the USA.
<P>
Yesterday the walkers blocked the two maingates of Cogema's
reprocessing factory at La Hague for over three hours.
<P>
They demand the phase-out of nuclear energy and ask the
autorities to invest money in energy efficiency and renewable
energy programs.
<P>
FOR MOTHER EARTH has chosen Cogema's crane to be the last
actionplace in France. Tomorrow they take the ferry at 5pm for
Portsmouth. The walkers plan to be in Chernobyl on August 6th for
the 50th commemoration of Hiroshima. They will end their walk on
October 12th 1995 before the Kremlin in Moscow.


<P>
<HR>
For more information, registrations and financial support:

<address>

FOR MOTHER EARTH International Gent, Belgium
Zilverhof 19, 9000 Gent, BELGIUM, Phone +32-9-233.32.68 , Fax +32-9-233.49.24 <BR>
E-mail: <A HREF="mailto: motherearth@knooppunt.be">motherearth@knooppunt.be</A> or walk@antenna.nl

</address><A HREF=/~fme/wae/waeidx.html>[INDEX]</A> <A HREF=wrep009.html>[NEXT]</A>

</body>
</html>




