<HEAD><TITLE> Walk action report 9  </TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/waeidx.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~fme/images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A> <A HREF="/~walk/contacta.html"><IMG SRC  = "contacta.gif" ALT="Contact Addresses"></A> <A HREF=wrep008.html><IMG SRC = "arrwleft.gif"></A><A HREF="wrepovv.html"><IMG SRC  = "actreprt.gif"  ALT="Action Report" ></A><A HREF=wrep010.html><IMG SRC = "arrwriht.gif"></A>

<H2>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</H2>
<H2>Cherbourg, February 17th 1995 </H2>


<HR>
<H1>PEACE WALKERS DENIED VISA FOR UK
 </H1>

<P>
<B>Seven peace walkers from Sri Lanka, three Ukrainians and two
Rumanians were refused access to the UK by the British Consulate
in Paris.
</B><P>

The walkers held a newsconference and symbolic action before
the customs in the Cherbourg harbor.
<P>
Aurel Duta, a participant from Rumania stated that "After having
received a visa for the Benelux and France without any problems, I
don't understand why the British Consul in Paris refused our
message of peace. Now I realize that so-called free countries
have things to hide. I feel deeply humiliated by the
treatment we received at the British Consulate in Paris."
<P>
Mr. Subramanidas Vanparambil Raman, coordinator of the Sri
Lankian walkers, stated that "People from Sri Lanka who wish
to buy British weapons probably receive all facilities to
visit the UK, while they refuse visas and hospitality to
people with a message of non-violence".
<P>
Concerning visas for Benelux the walkers have received
written support from former Belgian Minister of Foreign
Affairs Willy Claes (now Secretary General of NATO) and the
Belgian Minister of the Interior Johan vande Lanotte.
<P>
The walkers from Ukraine and Rumania will stay in France
and Belgium while the walk is in England, while the Sri Lankan
walkers decided to go back to Sri Lanka as they only planned
to stay another 10 days on the peace walk.
<P>
			-end-


<P>
<HR>
For more information, registrations and financial support:

<address>
FOR MOTHER EARTH International, Gent, Belgium
</address><A HREF=/~fme/wae/waeidx.html>[INDEX]</A> <A HREF=wrep010.html>[NEXT]</A>

</body>
</html>




