<HEAD><TITLE>Walk action report 10 - Ardermaston  </TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/waeidx.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~fme/images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A> <A HREF="/~walk/contacta.html"><IMG SRC  = "contacta.gif" ALT="Contact Addresses"></A> <A HREF=wrep009.html><IMG SRC = "arrwleft.gif"></A><A HREF="wrepovv.html"><IMG SRC  = "actreprt.gif"  ALT="Action Report" ></A><A HREF=wrep011.html><IMG SRC = "arrwriht.gif"></A>

<H2>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</H2>
<H2>Ardermaston, February 21st 1995 </H2>


<HR>
<H1>ANTI-NUKE WALKERS PROTESTED AT A.W.E'S ALDERMASTON
ALL GATES BLOCKADED FROM 7.15 am TILL 17.00 pm
 </H1>

<P>
<B>At Tuesday February 21st at 7.15 am 60 peace-
activists started to block all the entrances of the
nuclear base. Immediately the MOD locked the gates to
stop the activists coming in. Workers were not able
to enter the Aldermaston base as well. The maingate
was blocked by a living carpet of 25 people laying on
the road. There was a big trafficjam. In about 40
policemen were dragging away the activist in a
violent way. A group of people went inside the fences
but were soon kicked out again. No arrestations took
place.One Belgium girl was hit by a car. Many people
were injured by the policemen. Non-violent direct
actions continued all day through.
</B><P>

An international group of 50 peace-activists from
more then ten different countries has arrived in the
United Kingdom on February 17th.The walkers started
the 5500 km walk at the European Union in Brussels on
January 12th, and plan to arrive at the Kremlin in
Moscow on October 12th, the International Day of
Solidarity with Indigenous People.Today,Tuesday
February 21st they have an all-day action at the
Atomic Weapons Establishment in Aldermaston
Burghfield.
<P>
Since 1952 the United Kingdom's nuclear weapons have
been manufactured and researched at Aldermaston, near
Reading in Central England. Before the end of the
Cold War the U.K. began working on a new nuclear
weapons system called Trident. It was meant to be
used against the former Soviet Union.New warheads are
still being manufactured under unsafe circumstances,
both to the environment and to the people living
close or working at the base.
<P>
The actionday on Tuesday February 21st is organised
by local peace- and environmental groups and is
supported by approx. 40 peacewalkers of FOR MOTHER
EARTH.
<P>
The walkers demand a halt of nuclear testing, a
review and extention of the Non Proliferation Treaty
(the NPT conference takes place place in New York
next March), the phase out of nuclear power and the
development of sustainable energy. Next to the
social, economical and ecological consequences of the
nuclear age, they wish to highlight the fate of many
Indigenous People who have been affected by nuclear
developments (i.e. uranium mining, nuclear testing
and rad-waste).
<P>
Walkers are coming from Austria, Belgium, Canada,
Denmark, France, Germany, the Netherlands,
Switzerland, the United Kingdom and the United
States.
<P>
After walking in the UK they will take a ferry to
Belgium the 3th of March.The route continues through
Germany, Czech Republic, Austria, Slovakia, Ukraine,
Belarus and ends in Russia.
<P>
There are 7 persons from Sri Lanka, 2 Rumanians, 3
Ukrainians and 2 Americans who should have been on
this Peacewalk as well but they were refused access
to the UK by the British Consulate in Paris and the
Autorities in Portsmouth.
<P>
			-end-
<P>
<HR>
For more information, registrations and financial support:

<address>
FOR MOTHER EARTH International, Gent, Belgium
</address><A HREF=/~fme/wae/waeidx.html>[INDEX]</A> <A HREF=wrep011.html>[NEXT]</A>

</body>
</html>


