<HEAD><TITLE> Walk Action Report 12 - London</TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/waeidx.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~fme/images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A>

<H2>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</H2>
<H2>London, Monday February 13 1995</H2>


<HR>
<H1>FOR MOTHER EARTH ACTIVISTS OCCUPY OFFICES URANIUM INSTITUTE</H1>


<P>
<B>At 11.55am FOR MOTHER EARTH activists started a non-violent
occupation of the offices of the Uranium Institute (Bowater
House, 68 Knightsbridge, London SW1X 7LT - Phone 0171-
2250303). They will stop the occupation after a meeting with
the chairman or vice-chairman of the Uranium Institute.
</B><P>

The Uranium Institute comprises mining companies,
electricity utilities, and nuclear fuel processors and
traders from 20 countries (i.e. BNFL, RTZ, Urenco, Cogma,
Cameco, Euratom, Siemens, ...). The Uranium Insitute, also
known as the International Association for Energy from
Nuclear Fuel, aims to promote the use of uranium for
peaceful purposes, by the exchange of information and
research into issues affecting the civil uranium and nuclear
industries.
<P>
The activists demand that all uranium mining is stopped.
Outside the offices some activists are holding a banner
saying "Birds in the sky, fish in the water, uranium in the
ground". They also placed over fifty signs along the
sidewalk with the names of Indigenous People who are
affected by uranium mining. Seventy to eighty percent of all
uranium is mined on Indigenous Peoples land. FOR MOTHER
EARTH wants the Uranium Institute and all its members to
stop all nuclear activities, and to invest all their efforts
in promotion and use of sustainable energies.
<P>
The activists are part of the Walk across Europe for a
Nuclear-Free World. Today the walkers are heading from
Greenwich to Gravesend.
<P>
Walkers from Austria, Belgium, Blackfeet Indian Nation,
Britain, Bulgaria, Canada, Denmark, France, Germany, the
Netherlands, Rumania, Switzerland, Ukraine and the USA
started the 5.500 km walk at the European Union in Brussels
on January 12th 1995, and plan to arrive at the Kremlin in
Moscow on October 12th 1995, the International Day of
Solidarity with Indigenous People.
<P>
They demand a halt of nuclear testing, to outlaw nuclear
weapons and to phase out nuclear energy. They want the
extension and revision of the Non-Proliferation Treaty,
which is on the agenda of the UN in New York next April. A
Danish truck with a 50m2 exhibition on energy savings and
renewable energy is travelling along with the walkers.
<P>
			-end-


<P>
<HR>
For more information, registrations and financial support:

<address>
FOR MOTHER EARTH International, Gent, Belgium
</address><A HREF=/~fme/wae/waeidx.html>[INDEX]</A> <A HREF=wrep013.html>[NEXT]</A>

</body>
</html>


