<HEAD><TITLE> Day   1 - Kick Off in Brussels   </TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/waeidx.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~fme/images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A>
<A HREF=wrep001.html><IMG SRC = "/~fme/images/arrwleft.gif"></A>
<A HREF=wrepovv.html><IMG SRC  = "/~fme/images/actreprt.gif"  ALT="Action Report" ></A>
<A HREF=wrep001c.html><IMG SRC = "/~fme/images/arrwriht.gif"></A>

<H2>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</H2>
<H2>Brussel, January 12  </H2>

    Walk Across Europe for a Nuclear Free World<br>
		      & Sustainable Energy Tour '95

<HR>
<H1>Day 1 - Thu  January 12, 1995 - Kick-Off </H1>
<H3>
The Walk</H3>
<P>
At 11.00 AM about 100 Walkers gathered in front of the Mayors Hall in
Brussels. 60 of them were students, that joined the walk for a day
out of solidarity with a nuclear free world.
Around 14.00 the walkers reached the edge of Brussels and walked
their first steps of a 5.500 kilometer long walk that will end 12
October 1995 in Moscow.
The night was spent in Halle.

<P><H3>
The SET</H3>

After some trouble with permissions, the Exhibition was set up at 8.00
AM in Brussels. It was opened untill 17.00 PM
<P>
Tudor, who came from Romania to join the Walk, worked during the
basecamp on the SNORE-truck. During the exhibition in Brussels he
said: 'It's great ! It has a windmill and two solarpanels, so you can
really see what are renewables ! Inside, there are posters that
explain about energy savings and renewable sources... It's great !'


<P>
<HR>
For more information, registrations and financial support:

<address>

FOR MOTHER EARTH International, Gent, Belgium

</address><A HREF=/~fme/wae/waeidx.html>[INDEX]</A> <A HREF=wrep001c.html>[NEXT]</A>

</body>
