<HEAD><TITLE>Walk Across Europe Action Report   </TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/waeidx.html"><IMG SRC="/~fme/images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/reports/wrepovv.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~fme/images/actreprt.gif"  ALT="Action Report" ></A>
<p>

Sorry for delay of distribution of this message. Telephone line
in Russia are disturbing. E-mail and fax connection seemed
impossible. Thus we decided to travel to Moscow to communicate wit
the world.


<h2>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</h2>

<h2>Walkers protest at Smolensk NPP in Russia</h2>


Smolensk, September 18th 1995 - This morning 22 activists of th
international ecological group FOR MOTHER EARTH demonstrated fo
two hours at the NPP of Smolenskaya near Desnogorsk (Smolensk
Region) in Western Russia. Thi was the first demonstration ever at
this 1000-RBMK type NPP with three nuclear reactors, which
according to Krista van Velzen, spokesperson for the group is one
of the most dangerous in Russia.<p>

During a one hour meeting with a delegation of the group, th
director of the NPP admitted that since the disintegration of the
Soviet Union there are problems with the supply of spare parts.<p>

The activists of FME are part of the 'Walk across Europe for a
Nuclear-Free World'. This 5.500km walk will end in Moscow next
October 12th.<p>

In Russia the walkers receive support from the Smolensk Region
Youth Council, Greenpeace Russia, the Social Ecological Union,
IPPNW and the Transnational Radical Party.<p>

                              -end-

