<HEAD><TITLE>Walk Across Europe Action Report   </TITLE></HEAD>

<body>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/waeidx.html"><IMG SRC="/~fme/images/walkhome.gif" ALT="Walk Across Europe Home Page"></A>
<A HREF="/~fme/wae/reports/wrepovv.html"><IMG SRC  = "/~fme/images/actreprt.gif"  ALT="Action Report" ></A>
<p>

Press-contacts:
FOR MOTHER EARTH in Moscow
Pol D'Huyvetter     phone   978-4917 or 978-3173
                    fax     251-908
<p>
MEDIA-ADVISORY 
<p>
NEWSRELEASE AND MAP WAS ALREADY DISTRIBUTED!!

<h2>
      Walkers end 5.500 km anti-nuclear journey
              through Europe in Moscow </h2>
<pre>

Moscow, October 9th 1995 - Next Thursday October
12th about fifty walkers from fifteen different
countries will set the final steps in the 5.500 km
'Walk across Europe for a Nuclear-Free World' , an
initiative of the international group FOR MOTHER
EARTH.
 
10:00 a.m.      Moscovites join walkers at Gorki
                Monument at Belaruskaya Statio
 
11:15 a.m.      PRESSCONFERENCE 
                in Renewable Energy Exhibition
                trailer at main entrance Gorki Park
                (Ul. Krymsky Val)
 
11:45 a.m.      Walkers arrive at Gorki Park
 
12:00 a.m.      Visual boycott-action at Frenc
                embassy. Meeting with embassador'
                first adviser Francois Goldblatt
 
12:45 a.m.      Action at Minatom. Meeting wit
                Minister Michailov was requested.
 
13:30 a.m.      PHOTO-OPPORTUNITY!!!
                Walkers arrive at Kremlin
                Street-theatre in front of
                St-Basil's
                Meeting with Kremlin officials is 
                pendant.
                Walkers end action with lunch
 
NOTE!
The times are careful estimations. However 'walkin
through Moscow's traffic' may put the walkers 
little off schedule.
 
PLEASE CALL IF YOU WANT A PRESS-FIL
 
                        -end
 

