<br clear=left>
In their underground lab, Stuffed Babies on Wheels develop intergalactic science-fiction
coloured freak-fusion dance music: groovy sax-and hammondpieces with hot percussion.
Supported by funky and soulfull bas and drumstructures decorated with a wacky guitar.
Over this stormy lot, "The J" pours his rhymes. Seventies influences as soul & funk are
mixed with modern hip-hop and acid-jazz elements. The sound of the big city in full
activity. 
<p>
</td>
</tr>

