<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>  (engelstalig)
GENERAL INFORMATION (level 1)</TITLE>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="oww.jpg"></CENTER>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<hr>
<P>The Worlds Shops sell products from the Third World. We buy those products directly from organisations of small farmers and give them a fair price for it. That price is in proportion to the delivered efforts and is usually a bit above the common market price. For us, that is just a matter of respect.


<P>A guaranteed and endurable income makes sure that the small producers can build a decent existence. There can be put some work into solid housing, education and health services. Investments in new cultures and in mankind more friendly and ecologically more sound techniques open better perspectives for the small farmers.


<P>With their work the Worlds Shops want to point out, that there is a lot which upsets the balance between the rich North and the deprived South. Some structural changes that deal with the roots of the problems can lead to more justice. In Flanders there are 150 Worlds Shops. That means 150 crossroads of ideas, breeding places of democratic and multicoloured cooperation. Thousands of voluntary collaborators devote themselves to get a fair, peaceful, ecologically sound and tolerant society. They give you a hearty welcome.

<P><IMG SRC="yellowba.gif">
