<CENTER><H1>PACHAWO</H1>
<P><IMG SRC="rainban.gif">
<H3>European Action Camp for young people in World Shops<BR>
17 - 24 August 1996, Lichtaart - Belgium</H3></CENTER>
<IMG SRC="rainban.gif">
<P>
<H2>Practical information:</H2><BR>
<P>
<STRONG>Date: 17 to 24 August 1996 (we expect you at the camp on 17 August before 4 p.m.).(*)</STRONG>
<P>
<STRONG>Venue: De Hoge Rielen - Molenstraat 62 - 2460 Kasterlee (Lichtaart) - Belgium.</STRONG>
<P>
<STRONG>Registration-fee: ECU 110 (transport no included).(*)</STRONG>
<P>
To really make it a "camp", well stay in tents. You are invited to bring your own tent.
A limited number of extra tents is provided for.(*)
<P>
Also good to know is that all food will be vegetarian.

<H5>How to register?</H5><BR>

Closing date for registration is 15 June 1996.
<P>
Click on <STRONG>ADRESSES</STRONG> to find the name of the contact person and full address, phone and fax number. This person can tell you all about how to register in your country and has more information about the financial side of the matter.
<P>
<FONT SIZE=-1>*As soon as we receive your registration, we will send you a confirmation. More practical information will follow through your national contact person!</FONT>
<P>

<STRONG>Notice:</STRONG><BR>
we will keep a reserve list of all participants. If  you have registered and for any reason realize that 
you will not be able to participate, please contact us 
( your national contact person or Oxfam-Wereldwinkels in Belgium-see address below) 
as soon as possible.<BR>
