<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>CRITERIA ENGELS (level 2) </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P><CENTER><H1>Criteria.</H1></CENTER>
<P><HR ALIGN=center SIZE=2>
<P>Important guidelines, no dogma's.
<P>
<P>
<P>For a responsible choice of our products and producers we need a number of criteria, resulting from our vision on developement, underdevelopment and alternative trade.
<P>These explain how we think at the moment about a number of questions in the Third World and the answers states and groups try out there. They are guidelines, with which we try to find out in which degree a project or initiative contributes, according to us, to sustainable development.
<P>So the criteria render a value judgement, that is not necessary the same or beter than that of the producer-organisation concerned. We have te be consious of this to prevent a paternalistic attitude.
<P>On the other side clearly formulated criteria are a necessary handhold since we want to spent our engagment and limited means as meaningful as possible what implies a explicite choice.
<P>
<P>In reality no country or producergroup wil fulfil our expectations and criteria for a hundred percent. We'll always have to weigh the pro's and the contra's. Moreover projects and organisations are no constructions in a vacuüm. They are the result of the work of human beïngs who can make mistakes. They grew in a certain political and socio-economic context which can differ from country to country or even from project to project. In the end, it's this context that determines which criteria we can apply and in which degree we may expect a project to cope with them.
<P>
<P>In the end we distinguish four different kind of criteria who refer to <BR>
<!--Linken naar verschillende criteria-->
(a) <A HREF="ecrita.html"> the social significance of the partner</A><BR>
(b) <A HREF="ecritb.html"> the intern organisation of the partner</A><BR>
 (c) <A HREF="ecritc.html">the place of the product in the developmentproces </A> <BR>
 (d)<A HREF="ecritd.html"> the commercial possibilities of the product on our market </A>
<P>
<P>These criteria refer only to the Third World-products of Oxfam-Wereldwinkels.
<P>
<P>
<P><!--Knoppen naar vorige pagina en homepage-->
<CENTER><TABLE COLSPEC="L20 L20">
<TR>
<TD><A HREF="ecriteri.html"> <IMG SRC="terug.gif" ALT="Vorige Pagina"></A></TD>
<TD><A HREF="index.html"> <IMG SRC="index.gif" ALT="Homepage"></A></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

</BODY>
