<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> CRITERIUM A ENGELS (level 3) </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P><CENTER><H4>A. Social significance of the partner</H4>.</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>1. A good initiative <B>strengthens the social, political, economical or cultural capacities</B> of the producers. This implies that there are the beginnings of <B>emancipation and structural changes.</B>
<P>- Does the project work on the sympthons or on the roots of the problems?
<P>- Are solutions sought for the shortcoming or oppressive structures of intermediate trade, creditgrants, transport, agricultural advice etc...? 
<P>- Does the initiative aims at an integral approach with which there is attention for education, political awareness, teaching of reading and writing, health-care, housing, etc...
<P>- Does the project offer possibilities for women to improve their situation. 
<P>
<P>2. The initiative gives <B>preference to poor, oppressed or neglected groups</B> in society. 
<P>- It is difficult to reach, by means of the sell of products, the most marginal groups. Usually these do not make products, have no land to grow crops on. In case an initiative does work with marginalized groups, this is for us an extra motive to cooperate.
<P>- From the countries we support we expect that they use their economic surplus (the yields by production, export etc) to improve the living standard of the people and that the authorities care about the basic needs of the poorer groups in society.
<P>
<P>3. In principle the initiative is <B>open for new members</B> who subscribe the goals of the organisation and find themselves in a similar socio-economic position as the members themselves.
<P>- Do some of the projects of the organisation are favourable for non-members who find themselves in a similar or worse socio-economic position?
<P>- Does the group or organisation think it is important to coöperate with other initiatives who themselves too strive for the social emancipation of neglected or oppressed groups?
<P>
<P><!--Linken naar andere criteria in het Engels-->
(b) <A HREF="ecritb.html"> the intern organisation of the partner</A><BR> 
(c) <A HREF="ecritc.html">the place of the product in the developmentproces </A> <BR>
 (d)<A HREF="ecritd.html"> the commercial possibilities of the product on our market </A>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P><!--Knoppen naar vorige pagina en homepage-->
