<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> CRITERIUM B ENGELS (level 3)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P><CENTER><H4>B. Internal organisation of the partner.</H4></CENTER>
<P>
<P>
<P>Of great importance are:
<P>
<P>1. <B>Expert management.</B>
<P>- If not, in the end the producers will bear the burden. An amateurish development-project offers the producers false promises and brings down motivation. This is the reason for the need of a sound financial managment, strict quality-control, technical education of the producers, product-development, market-surveys etc...
<P>
<P>2. A <B>fair price/wage</B> for the producer's labour.
<P>- The judgement of the wage- or pricelevel is not a simpel question. We must take different factors into account such as internal purchasing power of the received amount of money, the wages/prices in similar sectors and situations, the marketvalue of the products, the degree of skilled labour, the number of working hours, other advantages the producers have such as free and/or sound education, healthcare, housing, etc...
<P>
<P>3. It is necessary that the <B>differences between wages are minimal.</B>
<P>
<P>4. It is important that <B>the share in the coststructure going to persons, enterprises and authorities situated between producers and consumers is not too big.</B> Therefore the chain between producers and consumers should be kept as short as possible.
<P>
<P>5. <B>Human working-conditions.</B>
<P>- Is there enough attention for the safety and the hygienic circumstances in which the producers work? Are there efforts to improve the working conditions, unionrights, social security and facilities...
<P>
<P>6.<B> Possibilities for all concerned to participate in the decissionmaking-proces on the policy and goals of the organisation.</B>
<P>- Do the producers have a say on the use of potential gains, investmentplans, the production proces, the tasksetting, the daily course of things etc...?
<P>- How big is the involvement of the producers in the realization of the project?
<P>
<P>7. It is an advantage when woman and men get equal chances or when initiatives are taken to stop the marginal position of women.
<P>
<P>8. <B>Meaningful use of potential gains.</B>
<P>- Is it being distributed in a fair way amongst all collegues?
<P>- Is it being invested in the further growth of the project?
<P>- Are other meaningful initiatives supported?
<P>
<P>9. To make a follow-up possible the partner must agree to <B>provide information </B>on its functioning regulary.
<P>
<P><!--Linken naar andere criteria in het Engels-->
(a) <A HREF="ecrita.html"> the social significance of the partner</A><BR>
(c) <A HREF="ecritc.html">the place of the product in the developmentproces </A> <BR>
 (d)<A HREF="ecritd.html"> the commercial possibilities of the product on our market </A>
<P>
<P>
