<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> CRITERIUM C ENGELS (level 3) </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P><CENTER><H4>C. Place of the product in the developmentproject.</H4></CENTER>
<P>
<P>The product must contribute to a proces of <B>sustainable development.</B>
<P>This implies:
<P>
<P>1. The product should <B>support the lokal economy and should not harm the foodsupply</B> of the local population.
<P>- Import of essential foodproducts of which there is a shortage in the land of production itself is difficult, unless there are specific reasons to legitimate such an import.
<P>- Neither do we want to stimulate the cultivation of exportcrops that might lead to shortages in the local foodproduction and consumsion.
<P>
<P>2. The more a product is<B> 'processed'</B> at the moment it is exported, the bigger the contribution to development usually is.
<P>For the producer it is usually an advantage if he can export a finished product. Each stage in the productionproces that takes place in the country itself creates work, an income, etc...
<P>
<P>
<P>3. The product should be produced in an <B>'environment-sound'</B>-way, considering the circumstances.
<P>- Are the raw materials environment-sound?
<P>- Is the packaging recycable or harmless for nature.
<P>- Is the use of chemical pesticides and fertilizers kept as minimal as possible?
<P>
<P>4. An initiative <B>should not be liveable due to the trade with the Wereldwinkels. The sell of products is</B> preferably <B>just a part of the activities of our partner.</B>
<P>
<P><!--Linken naar andere criteria in het Engels-->
(a) <A HREF="ecrita.html"> the social significance of the partner</A><BR>
(b) <A HREF="ecritb.html"> the intern organisation of the partner</A><BR>  
(d)<A HREF="ecritd.html"> the commercial possibilities of the product on our market </A>
<P>
<P>
<P><!--Knoppen naar vorige pagina en homepage-->
