<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> CRITERIUM D ENGELS (level 3) </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P><CENTER><H4>D. Commercial possibilities of the product on our market.</H4></CENTER>
<P>
<P>1. Products only meet with a large sale when they are of good quality.
<P>- The quality-standards should refer as well to the nutricious-value as to taste, sanity, tenability, packaging, etc...
<P>- Here consideration should be given to the technical possibilities of the country or project in question.
<P>
<P>2. A <B>good price/quality-ratio</B> makes a product sell beter.
<P>- When a product is too expensive, there will be no demand and we won't render a service to our partner by bringing it still on the market. We can use our limited means in a better way by investing in other products.
<P>
<P>3. It's evident that <B>there has to be a sufficiënt demand</B> for the product to make a profit by selling it.
<P>
<P>4. It is important that the producer can deliver the product <B>without interruption and in sufficiënt quantities.</B>
<P>
<P><!--Linken naar andere criteria in het Engels-->
(a) <A HREF="ecrita.html"> the social significance of the partner</A><BR>
(b) <A HREF="ecritb.html"> the intern organisation of the partner</A><BR>
 (c) <A HREF="ecritc.html">the place of the product in the developmentproces </A> <BR>
<P>
